### HMS — Staff Service API Collection
### Base URL: http://localhost:3003 (direct) or http://localhost:3000/staff (via gateway)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3003
@contentType = application/json

# ─── Prerequisites: Create a Department and Staff Member first ─────────────────
# Run the Department and Staff sections before testing Doctor and Allocation APIs

# ─── DEPARTMENTS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. List all departments
GET {{baseUrl}}/departments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 2. Create department — Cardiology
# @name createDept
POST {{baseUrl}}/departments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Cardiology",
  "description": "Heart and cardiovascular care"
}

###

### 3. Create department — Neurology
POST {{baseUrl}}/departments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Neurology",
  "description": "Brain and nervous system disorders"
}

###

### 4. Create department — General Physician
POST {{baseUrl}}/departments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "General Physician",
  "description": "Primary care and general medicine"
}

###

### 5. Create department — duplicate name (expect 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/departments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Cardiology"
}

###

### 6. Update department — set description
# Replace DEPT_ID with actual department UUID from step 2
@deptId = DEPT_ID_HERE

PUT {{baseUrl}}/departments/{{deptId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "description": "Updated: Advanced cardiovascular care and interventional cardiology"
}

###

### 7. Deactivate department
PUT {{baseUrl}}/departments/{{deptId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "is_active": false
}

###

### 8. Delete department — fails if active doctors assigned (expect 422)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/departments/{{deptId}}

###

# ─── DOCTORS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Note: POST /doctors uses multipart/form-data — use cURL or Postman for file uploads.
# The HTTP file shows the fields; avatar/banner are optional binary parts.

### 9. List all doctors
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 10. List doctors filtered by department
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors?department_id={{deptId}}&status=active
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 11. List doctors with search
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors?search=jenny&page=1&limit=10
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 12. Create doctor (multipart) — use cURL:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3003/doctors \
#   -F "first_name=Jenny" \
#   -F "last_name=Smith" \
#   -F "username=dr.jennysmith" \
#   -F "email=jenny.smith@hospital.com" \
#   -F "mobile=+94771234567" \
#   -F "password=Password@123" \
#   -F "date_of_birth=1985-05-20" \
#   -F "gender=female" \
#   -F "education=MBBS, MS" \
#   -F "designation=Senior Physician" \
#   -F "department_id=DEPT_ID_HERE" \
#   -F "biography=Experienced cardiologist with 15 years of practice." \
#   -F "address=123 Medical St" \
#   -F "city=Colombo" \
#   -F "country=Sri Lanka" \
#   -F "avatar=@/path/to/photo.jpg"

###

### 13. Create second doctor (multipart)
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3003/doctors \
#   -F "first_name=John" \
#   -F "last_name=Doe" \
#   -F "username=dr.johndoe" \
#   -F "email=john.doe@hospital.com" \
#   -F "mobile=+94770000001" \
#   -F "password=Password@123" \
#   -F "date_of_birth=1978-08-15" \
#   -F "gender=male" \
#   -F "education=MBBS, MD" \
#   -F "designation=Consultant Physician" \
#   -F "department_id=DEPT_ID_HERE"

###

### 14. Get doctor by ID
# Replace DOCTOR_ID with actual doctor UUID
@doctorId = DOCTOR_ID_HERE

GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 15. Get doctor — not found (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 16. Update doctor (multipart) — use cURL:
# curl -X PUT http://localhost:3003/doctors/DOCTOR_ID \
#   -F "designation=Chief Cardiologist" \
#   -F "biography=Updated biography text"

###

### 17. Deactivate doctor (soft-delete + Keycloak disable)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

# ─── SCHEDULES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reset doctorId to an active doctor before running these

### 18. Add Monday schedule (08:00–12:00, 15-min slots)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/schedule
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "day_of_week": 1,
  "start_time": "08:00",
  "end_time": "12:00",
  "slot_duration_minutes": 15,
  "max_patients": 16
}

###

### 19. Add Wednesday schedule (14:00–17:00, 20-min slots)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/schedule
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "day_of_week": 3,
  "start_time": "14:00",
  "end_time": "17:00",
  "slot_duration_minutes": 20,
  "max_patients": 9
}

###

### 20. Add Friday schedule (09:00–13:00, 30-min slots)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/schedule
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "day_of_week": 5,
  "start_time": "09:00",
  "end_time": "13:00",
  "slot_duration_minutes": 30,
  "max_patients": 8
}

###

### 21. Add schedule — invalid time range (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/schedule
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "day_of_week": 2,
  "start_time": "12:00",
  "end_time": "08:00",
  "slot_duration_minutes": 15,
  "max_patients": 10
}

###

### 22. Get doctor schedule
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/schedule
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 23. Get availability — Monday March 2, 2026 (16 slots for 15-min session)
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/availability?date=2026-03-02
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 24. Get availability — Wednesday March 4, 2026
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/availability?date=2026-03-04
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 25. Get availability — no schedule day (Tuesday, expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/availability?date=2026-03-03
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 26. Update schedule entry
# Replace SCHEDULE_ID with UUID from step 18
@scheduleId = SCHEDULE_ID_HERE

PUT {{baseUrl}}/schedules/{{scheduleId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "max_patients": 20,
  "slot_duration_minutes": 10
}

###

### 27. Deactivate a schedule entry
PUT {{baseUrl}}/schedules/{{scheduleId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "is_active": false
}

###

### 28. Delete schedule entry
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/schedules/{{scheduleId}}

###

# ─── STAFF MEMBERS (Nurses) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 29. Create nurse — Sarah Williams
# @name createNurse
POST {{baseUrl}}/staff
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "full_name": "Sarah Williams",
  "role": "nurse",
  "email": "sarah.williams@hospital.com",
  "mobile": "+94779876543",
  "status": "active"
}

###

### 30. Create nurse — Michael Chen
POST {{baseUrl}}/staff
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "full_name": "Michael Chen",
  "role": "nurse",
  "email": "michael.chen@hospital.com",
  "mobile": "+94778765432"
}

###

### 31. Create receptionist staff member
POST {{baseUrl}}/staff
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "full_name": "Alice Johnson",
  "role": "receptionist",
  "email": "alice@hospital.com",
  "mobile": "+94775555000"
}

###

### 32. List all staff members
GET {{baseUrl}}/staff
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 33. Get staff member by ID
# Replace NURSE_ID with UUID from step 29
@nurseId = NURSE_ID_HERE

GET {{baseUrl}}/staff/{{nurseId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 34. Get available nurses on a date (both Sarah and Michael should appear)
GET {{baseUrl}}/staff/available?date=2026-03-10&role=nurse
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

# ─── NURSE ALLOCATIONS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 35. List all allocations
GET {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 36. Allocate Sarah to doctor on March 10
# @name allocateNurse
POST {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
X-User-Name: admin

{
  "nurse_id": "NURSE_ID_HERE",
  "doctor_id": "DOCTOR_ID_HERE",
  "session_date": "2026-03-10"
}

###

### 37. Allocate same nurse again on same date (expect 422 NURSE_ALREADY_ALLOCATED)
POST {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "nurse_id": "NURSE_ID_HERE",
  "doctor_id": "DOCTOR_ID_HERE",
  "session_date": "2026-03-10"
}

###

### 38. Get available nurses — Sarah should be gone (allocated on March 10)
GET {{baseUrl}}/staff/available?date=2026-03-10&role=nurse
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 39. Allocate Michael to same doctor on a different date (allowed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
X-User-Name: receptionist1

{
  "nurse_id": "MICHAEL_ID_HERE",
  "doctor_id": "DOCTOR_ID_HERE",
  "session_date": "2026-03-12"
}

###

### 40. Filter allocations by doctor
GET {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations?doctor_id={{doctorId}}&status=active
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 41. Filter allocations by date
GET {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations?date=2026-03-10
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 42. Complete an allocation
# Replace ALLOCATION_ID with UUID from step 36
@allocationId = ALLOCATION_ID_HERE

PUT {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations/{{allocationId}}/complete
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 43. Complete already completed (expect 422)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations/{{allocationId}}/complete
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 44. Get available nurses — Sarah is free again after completion
GET {{baseUrl}}/staff/available?date=2026-03-10&role=nurse
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 45. Allocate nurse to non-existent doctor (expect 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "nurse_id": "NURSE_ID_HERE",
  "doctor_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "session_date": "2026-03-15"
}

###

### 46. Cancel an allocation
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations/{{allocationId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### 47. Cancel already completed allocation (expect 422)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/nurse-allocations/{{allocationId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

# ─── FULL WORKFLOW SUMMARY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. POST /departments          → Create Cardiology dept
# 2. POST /doctors (multipart)  → Create Dr. Jenny Smith + Keycloak account
# 3. POST /doctors/{id}/schedule → Add Monday 08:00-12:00 schedule
# 4. GET  /doctors/{id}/availability?date=2026-03-02 → See 16 slots
# 5. POST /staff                → Create nurse Sarah Williams
# 6. GET  /staff/available?date=2026-03-10 → Sarah is free
# 7. POST /nurse-allocations    → Allocate Sarah to Jenny on March 10
# 8. GET  /staff/available?date=2026-03-10 → Sarah no longer listed
# 9. PUT  /nurse-allocations/{id}/complete → Session done, Sarah freed
# 10. DELETE /doctors/{id}      → Deactivates doctor + Keycloak account
###
